text:
My personal big project in vanilla Minecraft (back in 1.4 beta) was what I called a Citadel, which was a 5x5 tower with an entire castle on top of it. Had to build cobblestone generator and have multiple furnaces running overtime to see it through.
Then I attempted building a water temple with an underwater glass tunnel leading into it, but back then there were no sea lanterns (as in non-fire based light sources, ended up making 1 block wide windows with flowing water behind them and glowstone blocks behind the water, but it didn't give nearly enough light to stop monsters from spawning there) and I also chose a spot that didn't really have enough place to house it without it being cramped, so I never finished it. Makes me a bit sad now that I reminesce about it.
